01:00.744 --> 01:01.711
Anybody here?

01:01.745 --> 01:02.679
Hello?

01:10.087 --> 01:11.122
Yo, what up?

01:11.155 --> 01:12.389
You've reached Tolbert!

01:12.422 --> 01:13.423
Hi!

01:13.456 --> 01:14.558
Go on and leave that message.

01:14.591 --> 01:15.625
You know what to do.

01:15.659 --> 01:17.394
Boop!

01:17.427 --> 01:18.129
Hey, Tolbert.

01:18.162 --> 01:19.729
Uh, It's Scott.

01:19.764 --> 01:22.399
Um, why did I come into
work today for nothing?

01:22.432 --> 01:24.769
You told me that we were
working a private party?

01:24.802 --> 01:26.804
Yeah, we are.

01:26.838 --> 01:27.704
Surprise!

01:29.140 --> 01:30.373
Hey!

01:30.407 --> 01:32.676
Bon voyage, buddy!

01:32.709 --> 01:33.845
Oh, thanks, man.

01:33.878 --> 01:35.545
I don't leave for a week.

01:35.579 --> 01:36.981
Yeah, I know, I know.

01:37.014 --> 01:39.083
But tonight's the only night
the restaurant's closed.

01:39.116 --> 01:40.852
Scotty!

01:40.885 --> 01:42.686
My main man, we are going to
miss you around here, brother.

01:42.719 --> 01:45.022
The place will not be
the same without you.

01:45.056 --> 01:46.389
Wow, thank you.

01:46.423 --> 01:47.457
That's... that's very
nice of you to...

01:47.490 --> 01:48.525
- It'll be a lot better!
- Oh!

01:48.558 --> 01:49.726
There it is.

01:49.760 --> 01:50.627
Aw, kidding.

01:50.660 --> 01:52.029
Kind of.

01:52.063 --> 01:53.396
But seriously, bro, I hope
that you make a better

01:53.430 --> 01:54.832
writer than you do a waiter.

01:54.866 --> 01:56.633
All right, Tolbert,
this place better

01:56.666 --> 01:58.568
be clean by opening tomorrow, or
you're doing doubles all week.

01:58.602 --> 01:59.971
Yep, yep.
Gotcha.

02:00.004 --> 02:01.005
All right.

02:01.038 --> 02:02.472
Uh, who are all these people?

02:02.505 --> 02:04.075
Oh, uh, these are
your friends, man.

02:04.108 --> 02:06.710
Happy birthday, Mike!

02:06.743 --> 02:08.478
Scott.

02:08.511 --> 02:09.713
Yeah.

02:09.746 --> 02:10.914
Look, you don't have
a lot of friends,

02:10.948 --> 02:12.549
so I had to improvise
a little bit.

02:12.582 --> 02:13.650
You know?

02:13.683 --> 02:14.785
All right.

02:14.819 --> 02:16.620
I invited some of
my improv class.

02:16.653 --> 02:17.889
She might know you.

02:17.922 --> 02:18.856
But let's just get a drink.

02:18.890 --> 02:20.157
OK.

02:20.191 --> 02:21.092
Oh, yeah.

02:21.125 --> 02:23.127
There we go!

02:23.160 --> 02:24.929
Ah, wait.

02:24.962 --> 02:28.766
To my best friend, who, uh, I
don't really understand why he

02:28.799 --> 02:30.835
has to move to become
a writer, but I guess

02:30.868 --> 02:32.036
it worked for Hemingway.

02:32.069 --> 02:33.637
So bottoms up.

02:33.670 --> 02:34.939
Actually, can we not
talk to Hemingway, though?

02:34.972 --> 02:38.742
Because he ended up
blowing his brains out.

02:38.776 --> 02:40.177
I'mma Google that.

02:40.211 --> 02:41.711
All right.

02:41.745 --> 02:42.980
Look, look, here's to a
better ending than that.

02:43.014 --> 02:43.948
- OK.
- OK?

02:43.981 --> 02:44.916
Thank you.

02:47.651 --> 02:48.518
Ooh!

02:48.551 --> 02:49.519
Come on, one more.

02:49.552 --> 02:51.155
Ooh, ooh.

02:51.188 --> 02:52.123
Hold up.

02:55.927 --> 02:56.794
Hey, Dad.

02:56.827 --> 02:58.095
Can I call you back?

02:58.129 --> 02:59.830
I'm actually... I'm at
a going away party.

02:59.864 --> 03:02.465
Scott, it's Cookie.

03:02.499 --> 03:04.902
I'm using your father's phone.

03:04.936 --> 03:09.106
I'm afraid your
father passed away.

03:09.140 --> 03:10.573
What?

03:10.607 --> 03:12.709
He died in his sleep.

03:12.742 --> 03:14.477
I called the crematorium.

03:14.511 --> 03:16.147
They're... they're coming in
two hours if you'd like to see

03:16.180 --> 03:19.817
him before they take him away.

03:19.850 --> 03:21.584
Daddy's dead?

03:21.618 --> 03:22.954
And
Scott, can... can you

03:22.987 --> 03:24.121
pick up your sister on the way?

03:41.839 --> 03:43.274
Hi.
Is he still here?

03:43.307 --> 03:44.809
Am I too late?

03:44.842 --> 03:46.143
No, he's still in bed,
right where I found him.

03:46.177 --> 03:48.745
OK.

03:48.779 --> 03:49.947
Where's Cindy?

03:49.981 --> 03:52.216
Uh, she stayed in the car.

04:46.804 --> 04:48.072
Drink warm water.

04:48.105 --> 04:49.840
Let cookie massage her legs.

04:49.874 --> 04:50.908
Avoid ice cubes.

04:50.941 --> 04:51.842
Really?

04:51.876 --> 04:53.144
They hurt his teeth.

04:53.177 --> 04:54.311
His teeth?

04:54.345 --> 04:55.678
The man's blood was
50% cholesterol.

04:55.712 --> 04:56.881
He's worried about his teeth?

04:56.914 --> 04:58.282
You know your
father and medicine.

04:58.315 --> 05:00.117
He thought if he saw a
doctor, they'd just find

05:00.151 --> 05:01.318
more things wrong with him.

05:01.352 --> 05:03.087
Yeah, isn't that
kind of the point?

05:03.120 --> 05:06.023
Uh, your father loved
that picture of her.

05:11.362 --> 05:13.730
Well, uh, I hope you
don't mind, but I

05:13.764 --> 05:18.035
collected a few personal items
that I thought you should have.

05:18.069 --> 05:19.870
So this is it, huh?

05:19.904 --> 05:21.839
A man's life reduced to
a 10 by 12 cardboard box.

05:21.872 --> 05:23.140
Oh, no.
That's not it.

05:23.174 --> 05:24.208
Wait a minute.

05:26.944 --> 05:28.846
I also made you a
tuna fish sandwich.

05:46.130 --> 05:49.400
Can you just take this?

05:49.433 --> 05:50.633
Thank you.

06:00.945 --> 06:03.347
Are you OK?

06:03.380 --> 06:04.315
Mom made me a sandwich.

06:07.318 --> 06:08.752
Yeah.

06:08.786 --> 06:11.288
Yeah, me, too.

06:11.322 --> 06:12.923
She's big on the sandwiches.

06:12.957 --> 06:14.358
Although Cookie's not
your mom, you know.

06:14.391 --> 06:16.160
She's... she's Dad's wife.

06:16.193 --> 06:20.663
Or she's Dad's
widow now, I guess.

06:20.697 --> 06:21.799
But you have a mom, right?

06:21.832 --> 06:22.900
So just don't ever
forget that, OK?

06:22.933 --> 06:23.834
You're right.

06:23.868 --> 06:25.735
I'm sorry.

06:25.769 --> 06:27.737
I mean, after everything
that Mom did for you,

06:27.771 --> 06:29.340
can you just please not
call Cookie Mom ever again?

06:29.373 --> 06:30.808
All right!
I said I'm sorry!

06:51.962 --> 06:54.231
We need to make a memorial card.

06:54.265 --> 06:55.432
What?

06:55.466 --> 06:56.800
A memorial card...
you can write it,

06:56.834 --> 06:59.236
and I can draw a picture.

06:59.270 --> 07:00.237
A memorial card?

07:00.271 --> 07:01.205
Who are we going to send...

07:07.811 --> 07:09.880
Yes, OK.

07:09.914 --> 07:11.348
That's a good idea.
Let's make a memorial card.

07:11.382 --> 07:13.184
Yeah, you can write it,
and I can draw a picture.

07:13.217 --> 07:14.151
OK, sure.

07:20.357 --> 07:23.060
My neighbor
watches TV so loud all night.

07:23.093 --> 07:25.229
I have to wear earplugs.

07:25.262 --> 07:28.132
And when I complain,
she screams at me.

07:28.165 --> 07:31.468
And she drinks a lot.

07:31.502 --> 07:34.338
I'm
sorry to hear it.

07:34.371 --> 07:36.006
What do you think I should do?

07:36.040 --> 07:39.076
I don't know, get
bigger earplugs?

07:39.109 --> 07:39.977
No, you're right.

07:40.010 --> 07:42.745
I should just ignore it.

07:42.780 --> 07:44.515
Do you want my sandwich?

07:44.548 --> 07:46.517
I don't like tuna fish.

07:46.550 --> 07:47.484
Me, neither.

07:52.089 --> 07:54.458
I hope Cookie doesn't put
Dad's ashes in one of these.

08:05.836 --> 08:07.137
I really just...

08:07.171 --> 08:08.839
I can't believe that Dad
wanted to be cremated.

08:08.872 --> 08:10.207
Why not?

08:10.241 --> 08:14.345
He never struck me as
a cremation type of guy.

08:14.378 --> 08:16.847
What would you do instead?

08:16.880 --> 08:21.285
I would have a burial like
a normal person in a box

08:21.318 --> 08:23.487
with a funeral in the ground.

08:24.989 --> 08:29.426
I'm sorry if that's
old school for you.

08:29.460 --> 08:31.228
OK, I get it.

08:31.262 --> 08:32.830
That's so boring!

08:32.863 --> 08:36.467
OK, what would you like
to do when you die, then?

08:36.500 --> 08:38.135
I don't know.

08:38.168 --> 08:42.573
I read about this thing where
they can take your ashes

08:42.606 --> 08:45.142
and turn them into a diamond.

08:45.175 --> 08:47.311
A diamond?

08:47.344 --> 08:49.546
A diamond.

08:49.580 --> 08:52.983
So you'd like to be
turned into a diamond?

08:53.017 --> 08:55.552
It beats being stuck in
a box for all eternity.

08:55.586 --> 08:57.454
OK, so... well, then what
happens to the diamond, then?

08:57.488 --> 08:58.389
Who gets that?

08:58.422 --> 08:59.823
I don't know.

08:59.857 --> 09:02.192
If I give it to you,
would you pawn me?

09:02.226 --> 09:03.127
The joke's on you...

09:03.160 --> 09:04.028
I won't even be here.

09:04.061 --> 09:04.995
I'll be in Paris.

09:07.598 --> 09:08.532
Right.

09:13.537 --> 09:15.039
I mean, I'm going
to come and visit you.

09:15.072 --> 09:15.839
Yeah.
Whatever!

